{
  "stem": "20686.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If I would go past number 30, I took my life into my own hands.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was more traditional.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, you know, she was influenced.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think my father was a stronger personality.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father-- and my father and my mother, I-- I-- sometimes they talk about here generation gap.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My grandparents, my both-- my both zaides, my both grandfathers, who were deep, traditional religious people, they could not understand.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And all of a sudden they have a son and a daughter, who don't want to have a [NON-ENGLISH], who became just the opposite, who had rebelled at everything that-- which was traditional.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and-- and in their rebellion, the animosity was so strong that they also lost the charm and the beauty of-- of traditionally Jewish life, which was trampled over by them.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- they-- they could not find a-- a-- a gold middle.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Do you understand?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Did you celebrate any Jewish festivals?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We celebrated Pesach, but also we gave it an modern explanation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father was a yeshiva broker before he was-- became a political-orientated man.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he-- he knew how to-- how to explain.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and in fact, I believe now, although I am not anymore political-- I have nothing to do with political movements-- I believe that Judaism, the way I understand it, was primarily a secular philosophy.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Religiosity became-- was part-- came later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's the way I understand.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If you-- if you divorce from Judaism, the mythology, you still retain a viable philosophy by which men can build a-- a new life, a-- a just society.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's the way I understand it.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
